storyInfo: Skadi has shredded hundreds of these monsters on her own. On the verge of exhaustion, she meets the young Inquisitor once again. The Inquisitor wants to take her away, but the locals do not let her.

attributes.text: The wandering singer closes the bulky box and carries it on her back again.
She takes one step and then another. The pile of limbs and coagulated fluids beneath her feet instantly rot and weather away.
On her third step, as the hems of her dress flutter in the sea breeze, the tiny particles of crystal scattered all across the ground disperse into the air as well.

attributes.content: D-Did you see that just now?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: I saw all of it.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: How did she even do that?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: She is a singer...
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Inquisitor, this is nothing strange for her. That's something she's always been capable of.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Singer... what? You're still calling her by that name?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: How else should I call her? You're the Inquisitor. You tell me.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I need to go outside.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Hey, wait!
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: What are you doing? So you think you can stop me too? I am an Inquisitor!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: What is this... So slimy...
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Phew... I-I got it! I landed a blow! That was close, Inquisitor.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Thank goodness you smashed this chair to pieces. It gave me a weapon when I needed one to smack this thing. It would've climbed on top of you otherwise!
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Y-You...! All of you are out of your minds!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: How could you not be scared, seeing these things?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: I was. Just a little. They're not as scary as you, though.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: You... How dare you compare me to these monsters?!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Fine, I won't argue with you. You haven't seen them before, and you have no idea what they are capable of. It's no wonder you are not scared.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Wait, the other inhabitants are coming outside. They... What are they doing?!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: They're not scared at all either...
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: The problem...
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: I need to find where this problem lies...
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.text: The problem, as the Inquisitor sees it, is the most abnormal sight she sees unfolding before her eyes.
The Inquisitor looks at the girl standing before her. Then, she looks over at the lone Ægir standing outside.
Finally, she turns her gaze to the inhabitants now lining into the streets.

attributes.content: Sand.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant D

attributes.content: Salt... So salty.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant C

attributes.content: That thing just now. You can eat it. It's gone. A shame.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant D

attributes.content: Too bad.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant C

attributes.content: You can eat salt.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant D

attributes.content: Yes, it's edible.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant C

attributes.content: More. More... Mhmm, blurgh.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant D

attributes.content: It's dirty.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant C

attributes.content: Swallow it. More...
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant D

attributes.content: Stop right there!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: I still have questions for you, and you will answer them—What do you mean, they're here for you?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: I'm bleeding.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: I can tell that much. You were wounded in your fight with the High Inquisitor, so you ran away. How's that got anything to do with these... monsters showing up?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: They can smell my blood.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: They're here to... kill you? I saw them all dashing toward you—
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Perhaps.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Perhaps?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: They can't hurt me.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Y-You! Do you know how annoying the way you talk is?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: It's the truth.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: They—I mean these monsters—They're gone.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Yes.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: They're all gone without a trace, as if they never were. If I didn't see them clearly with my own eyes, I would've thought this all a dream.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: These monsters... the Sea Terrors. I've come across them plenty of times before. They don't look that much like these ones, but they have that same disgusting stench.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: But that was on the beach, and they never show up in such numbers. Do you mean to tell me they do not actually live in the sea?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: They only show up when someone goes look for trouble at the shore, right? Just like what you were doing during the day.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: And now they came this far away from the beach. They've nearly made it to the streets.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: They can make it far more places than you can imagine. They can spread by changing form, permeating every corner of the world.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Be it iron-forged cities, villages built atop the highlands, or barrenlands with nothing but sand. Wherever one can go, they can too.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: How is that possible?!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: The world is surrounded by ocean. Just because you cannot see the ocean does not mean that the land where you stand will forever remain untouched by its waters. The seas are alive and ever flowing, and so are the calamities they bring with them.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: I know there are places where the seas are dangerous, but I didn't know that the danger existed... in the lands outside Iberia too.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Danger exists everywhere.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Still, these calamities are here because of me. If you come any closer, you will be affected too.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: You... Just who are you?!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: I already told you.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Enough with the wandering singer thing! I saw it all.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: You were fighting them, and you know exactly how to fight them too.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: When you finished them off, your technique was so much better than when you were fighting the High Inquisitor and me.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: I don't have quite the same handle on fighting humans.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: A-Ahem... Let's dispense with the strange talk... I know you are a strange one, but still...
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Were you... a hunter? I can kind of see that in your eyes.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: If you think I am, then sure.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: And you hunted these... Sea Terrors before?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: They need to be eliminated.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Ugh... The way you talk just grates me so much, but—I don't even know why—coming from you, this doesn't sound like a lie at all.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Singer, hunter... It doesn't matter to me what you were.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Going by the circumstances, I suppose you saved not just my life, but everyone who lives on this street, maybe even the entire town.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: You may be the enemy of my enemy, but that does not make you a friend.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: No matter the case, I need to do my job. I have to take you away.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: You were asking me what I am doing here.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: I am here to seek an answer, and this answer only has to do with me... and the person I am looking for.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: You wouldn't tell me a thing earlier.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: You didn't give me a chance to tell you.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: You may have given me an answer now, but that doesn't mean my judgment has changed.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: You don't belong to this city. A person like you showing up is a mistake.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Not to mention... You told me yourself you brought this disaster with you.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: —It's certainly not how I imagined it, though.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Nonetheless, Ægir. You are dangerous. You are a danger to this city. At the same time, this city is also a danger to you.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Hm?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Look at them. They are... eating scraps of the Sea Terrors' remains. They don't fear these monsters... No, they don't even know what monsters are.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: They feed when they are hungry. As a monster does. And humans... humans know what fear is.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: So... Are they still human?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: All I know is that they're trying their best to live.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: From that perspective, there's nothing that sets humans and monsters apart.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: When they live like that... can you really say they are alive?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: The High Inquisitor told me to see it for myself, and only now do I understand what he meant.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: In this city, the biggest problem isn't whatever its citizens are doing. It's that they are still alive in this manner—This is the most abnormal thing of all.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Like you, they are dangerous, and this danger must be kept under control, just like how mistakes must be corrected.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: You haven't given up.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Now I really can't let you go.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: I already told you. I still have something to take care of, and I am in a hurry.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Looks like we will have to do this again, then.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Ægir, I know you are hurt, and you must be exhausted after fighting the Sea Terrors.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: But I will not go easy on you.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: What's this? A small shell?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: It wasn't you, Ægir... You wouldn't throw this at me.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Perhaps one of the locals vomiting their guts out on the floor? No, it can't be them. They don't even know what it is they are stuffing into their mouths. They wouldn't move against me.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Is it... from the window over to the side?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Who is it?!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Who threw this? Step forward!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Hahh...
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: You? Did you throw this at me? Are you still trying to get in my way, to protect this Ægir?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Uh, yes! It's me!
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Anita, stop it with your nonsense.
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: Grandma Petra?! Y-You should stay inside...
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I did it, Your Honor.
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: Did you just call me 'Your Honor?'
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: I know who exactly you are. These ones know nothing.
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: There's someone still sane here...?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Old woman, perhaps your eyes aren't as good as they used to be. Please step back. We are taking care of something dangerous here.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Look, Your Honor. My eyes are as perfect as they can be. Even if the sky's pitch black, I will have no trouble hitting you as long as you forget to dodge.
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: Oh, tiny seashells, beautiful waves♪
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: One shell after another, one beating wave after another...
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: You admitted it yourself. Now I must—
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Inquisitor... Your Honor! Grandma Petra's sick... Please don't blame her?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: She's sick? No wonder. Yes, I can see that.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Oh, Little Anita. Enough nonsense. How am I sick?
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: Grandma Petra, please stop. Please.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Sick... sick!
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: What's sick is Sal Viento itself! Yes—This place, and all its people! And you, almighty Inquisitor... You are sick as well!
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: You, take your senile grandmother home.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: I have more important things to deal with.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: What important things? What's more important than being alive?
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: As an Inquisitor, there are things that I have to safeguard even with my life. For example, all the things that the law says are correct... as well as our country itself.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: You will use your life... to safeguard whose life?
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: I... Whatever... I shouldn't waste any more of my time with you. Your old age and your illness have done a number on your faculties, citizen. I can overlook your crazy behavior so long as you stand aside and let me take care of what's important.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Your Honor, I'm afraid I don't understand this right or wrong, this country of yours.
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: I just want to ask you this. This thing you are trying to uphold. We were never part of it, isn't that right?
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: What...?!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: You Inquisitors took our people away. You said they were disrupting order, that they assaulted someone while they were stealing food. They just wanted to live.
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: That wasn't me... but if they committed a crime, then that's how it should be.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: And they've never been back.
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: You brought your bad guys away, but did that improve our lives?
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: When you remove all the factors that bring chaos to society in time, there will naturally be order.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Yet there is less and less food to go by... Those of us who got on in years either die of hunger or disease. Even some of our young couldn't endure.
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: You speak of order... but all you want is for us to die quietly, isn't it? That way, there will be no more noise, and you upper class folks can finally lie down on your fluffy beds for a quiet night of sleep.
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: That's not it.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: All of Iberia is suffering. Not just you.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Shouldn't a criminal who steals resources and harms the people be stopped? Suppose there are ten meals before us. They should feed ten Iberians.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: If no one is there to tell them how much they should get, they will fight to no end. In the end, only one of the ten will remain.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: The Inquisition draws the boundary of right and wrong amid this chaos and guides the masses to the right path. Otherwise the whole country would've long become a heap of sand.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Everything you said... I don't get it, and it's nothing I can see.
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: We don't have a way out. When we truly wanted one, where were you?
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: I... I want to help you. I am working hard to become a full-fledged Inquisitor. I took this path because I want to help the people, and I trust that this is the only way.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Help us...?
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: I hoped, imagined, thirsted, even dreamt of someone coming to save us. I screamed through so many nights till my throat was hoarse.
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: You never came.
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: Will you Inquisitors only come when someone has done something wrong?
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: Look at these old bones. I never imagined I'd live this long. What a tragedy. Every day is filled with nothing but pain.
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: Look, I'm attacking you, Your Honor.
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: Take me away! Take me, and end me! Put me out of my misery!
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: Hurry, do it! I can't wait no longer—I've waited all these years! *Cough* *cough*...
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: I don't want to fight you. Your anger... is understandable. My sword should not...
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Don't force my hand, citizen.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: *Cough* *Cough*...
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: Grandma!
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Oh... Anita... You came to the plaza too.
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: It's dark... Why is there no singing yet?
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: Singer, you said you are a singer. Why aren't you singing? Where is your harp? I want to dance. I need a tune.
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: Look, Your Honor. You're more useless than a wandering singer. She sings for us. She's even brave enough... to stand in front of the rest of us.
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: I'm not scared of monsters, and I'm not scared of death. What I am scared of is this life. Am I crazy, Anita?
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: Grandma, it's okay. You're shaking. It's cold here. Why don't we go back? Lie down and get some rest. You'll feel better.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Okay... Okay. Let's go. We'll go home. It isn't like I know where else to go anyway.
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: You...!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Did you change your mind? If you changed your mind, you can still take me away. That, or kill me. At the very least... I would get to die like a person.
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: Do it while I'm still alive, Your Honor. I don't have much time left.
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: Come, let's go... Singer, come with us. I want to hear you sing.
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: I will let you go... for now.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: But I will be back!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: And you, Ægir! I'm watching you, and I will get to the end of this! Don't think you can get out of this one!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Phew... That was close.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Singer, are you okay? You look white as a sheet.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I'm fine.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: You don't need to act so tough anymore. The Inquisitor is gone.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I'm not afraid of her.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: I know. I can tell you aren't afraid. What would someone like you be afraid of?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: She's not a bad person.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: And it would be a good thing for you if I leave this place.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: A good thing? There's nothing good here.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Grandma might've said all that, but she doesn't really hate the Inquisitor. She hates something else. I know it.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Now dance. Haha, I love your singing...
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: Stop spinning around, Grandma. You're tired. The singer will sing for you. Isn't that right?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Give me your hand, singer. Let me take a look at your wound.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: No...
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: I can't come near you because it's dangerous, right?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: It's okay. I trust you. If anything happens, you will win.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Look, your wounds aren't so bad at all. No more bleeding.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Singer, you are amazing. You heal up so quickly.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: It could've been quicker.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: But even so, you don't look well to me, and the house you picked was blown to pieces. I doubt even you can get a good sleep there now. Why don't you come home with me and Grandma Petra?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: That's right. Stay with us. Don't let them come look for any more trouble with you.
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: No...
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Okay, enough 'No's, 'No need's, and 'I have other things to do.' I am sick of them.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I can still...
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Ugh...
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Look at you. Out of strength, no? You need someone to look after you, and you definitely need some sleep.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I also think the person you're looking for probably doesn't want to see you pushing yourself like this.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: What was that... just now?
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: None of my business anymore...
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: I shouldn't ask questions. I have my answer now. I know the way. I know where to go.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: I need to go straight... Straight ahead.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: Tomorrow, everyone will have food to eat. I... No, we... All of us will get to live.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: 'We want to survive, so we must love one another even more.'
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: 'For love is the inseparable bond between us.'
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: 'I will become stronger.'
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: 'Our people will likewise become stronger.'
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.text: The man limps forward toward the pitch-black seas until he comes upon an object blocking his way.

attributes.content: This...
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: Her harp. It's here.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: (Tries to play the harp like Skadi does)
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: (Chords)
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: Sounds horrible.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: This is useless. I will leave it here to rot.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A
